Package teal.math

Provides the integration model and the generalized classes for performing different integration schemes, and also defines special functions, for example elliptical integrals, and also defines geometry objects, for example planes using the Point Normal form.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    GridIterator
    provides an interface for classes that iterate over a rectangular region.
    Integratable
    This interface should be implemented by TealObjects that need to have their properties updated via numerical integration.
    MetaIntegratable
    This interface extends Integratable, and should be implemented by those TealObjects that need to be integrated, but might have internal variables that are interdependent.
    VectorIterator
    VectorIterator: Interface for producing a sequence of Vector3d values.

    Plane
    Creates a plane using the Point Normal form (p0,normal) and carries out various functions.
    PlaneIterator
    Randomly selects points on the plane
    RectangularPlane
    Creates a plane with special properties.
    RungeKutta4
    Fourth order Runge-Kutta integration implementation.

Package teal.math Description
